numberOfPolls: The number of polls that we found for the country in dataset 1.
NumberOfInternetUsers: The number of internet users within the country according to the CIA World Fact Book (https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/rankorder/2153rank.html), or according to the Internet World stats (http://www.internetworldstats.com).
NumberOfPollsPerInternetUser: The number of polls divided by the number of Internet users.
GDPpercapitaIn$: The GDP per capita in US dollars according to the CIA world factbook.
WVS: The scores for each country from the World Value Survey.
PDI: Hofstede’s Power Distance scores for each country.
IDV: Hofstede’s Individualism scores for each country.
OverallPaceMeans: The Z score per country as calculated on the basis of walking speed, postal speed, and clock accuracy by Levine and Norenzayan.
planningahead_numberofpolls: The number of polls for which we found a time stamp, and could thus analyze the advance planning time.
planningahead_meanminutes: average advance planning time in minutes across all polls per country.
planningahead_min_minutes: minimum advance planning time across all polls per country.
planningahead_max_minutes: maximum advance planning time across all polls per country.
planningahead_stderror: standard error of average advance planning time across all polls per country.
responsetime_numberofpolls: The number of polls for which we found a time stamp, and could thus analyze the average response time per poll and country.
responsetime_mean: The average response time per country.
responsetime_stdError: The standard error of the average response times across all polls per country.
responsetime_numberofpolls_open: The number of open polls for which we found a time stamp, and could thus analyze the average response time per poll and country.
responsetime_numberofpolls_hidden: The number of hidden polls for which we found a time stamp, and could thus analyze the average response time per poll and country.
